<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Security Control Simulation System</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/style.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="/public/assets/favicon.webp" type="image/x-icon">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .custom-navbar {
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        .navbar-logo a {
            color: #ecf0f1;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        .info {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 2rem auto;
            padding: 2rem;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }
        .important-note {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #e74c3c;
        }
        #continue {
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }
        #continue:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
        }
        .img-container {
            margin-top: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <nav class="custom-navbar">
        <div class="navbar-logo">
            <a href="#">SCSS</a>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="info" id="webgazerInstructions">
        <h1>WebGazer Eye Tracking Calibration</h1>
        <h2>Please allow webcam access before starting the calibration.</h2>

        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Initial view.</p>
                <div class="img-container text-center">
                    <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions1.png" alt="Initial view" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Focus and begin left mouse clicking on one blue square.</p>
                <div class="img-container text-center">
                    <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions2.png" alt="Clicking on blue square" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>The square will turn red when calibrated.</p>
                <div class="img-container text-center">
                    <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions3.png" alt="Calibrated red square" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <p>Look at the screen with blue squares as shown in the first image.</p>
        <p>Focus on one blue square at a time.</p>
        <p>While looking at the square, click on it 5 times.</p>
        <p>Keep your gaze on the square until it turns red.</p>
        <p>Move to the next blue square and repeat steps 2-4.</p>
        <p>Continue until all squares have turned red.</p>
        <p class="important-note">For optimal eye tracking performance, maintain your focus on only the square you are clicking on throughout the process.</p>
        <button type="button" id="continue">Continue</button>
    </div>

    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="/public/scripts/webgazer.js"></script>
    <script>
        document.getElementById("continue").addEventListener("click", () => {
            window.location.href = '/information/webgazerconfig';
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>